
[1]sabianism

   SABIANISM, n. That species of idolatry which consisted in worshiping
   the sun, moon and stars. This idolatry existed in the world, and was
   propagated by the inhabitants who migrated westward into Europe, and
   continued among our ancestors till they embraced the christian
   religion.
